n AICTE approved Technical institution at Degree/ Diploma. Total 4000 scholarship are given @ Rs. 30000 as tuition fee reimbursement and Rs. 20000 as incidentals each year. Students can now Apply Online for Pragati Scheme to avail its benefits.  \n [View Details](https://www.aicte-india.org/sites/default/files/combine%20pragati%20%26%20saksham.pdf)  \n [Apply Online](https://www.aicte-india.org/schemes/students-development-schemes/batch-2019-2020-pragati)", "005-listElement": "- **Saksham Scholarship Scheme** \u2013 Saksham Scholarship / Contingency is awarded to differently abled students taking admission in AICTE approved Technical institution at Degree/ Diploma. Total 1000 scholarship are given @ Rs. 30000 as tuition fee reimbursement and Rs. 20000 as incidentals each year. Students can now Apply Online for Saksham Scheme to avail its benefits.  \n [View Details](https://www.aicte-india.org/schemes/students-development-schemes/General-Instructions)  \n [Apply Online](https://www.aicte-india.org/schemes/students-development-schemes/batch-2019-2020-saksham)", "006-listElement": "- **Prerana Scheme for Preparing SC / ST Students for Higher Education** \u2013 There is an acute shortage of faculty in engineering & polytechnic colleges. The problem can be addressed by promoting degree students of pre-final and final year to go for post graduate courses. Prerana Scheme aims at providing financial support to institutes who are willing to put extra efforts for encouraging and training SC/ST students for GATE/GPAT/CAT/CMAT and GRE. The broad objective of the scheme is to help aspiring SC/ST students seeking higher education through admission test like GATE/GPAT/CAT/CMAT/ TOEFL/ IELTS and GRE. Students can Apply Online for Prerana Scheme to avail its benefits.  \n [View Details](https://www.aicte-india.org/sites/default/files/Prerana.pdf)  \n [Apply Online](https://www.aicte-india.org/sites/default/files/User_Manual_-_AQIS_Application_-_PRERANA_OUI.pdf)", "007-listElement": "- **Samriddhi Scheme for SC / ST Students for Setting Start-Ups** \u2013 Looking at the poor job availability in the market, it is necessary to provide opportunities for SC/ST students to start their own enterprise. The broad objective of Samriddhi Scheme is to help SC/ST students is in designing, launching and running their own business/startup through entrepreneurship development programme after formal education is over/during their education as per AICTE\u2019s startup policy. Students can Apply Online for Samriddhi Scheme to avail its benefits.  \n [View Details](https://www.aicte-india.org/sites/default/files/Samiridhi.pdf)  \n [Apply Online](https://www.aicte-india.org/sites/default/files/User_Manual_-_AQIS_Application_-_SAMRIDDHI_OUI.pdf)", "008-listElement": "- **Support to Students for Participating in Competition Abroad (SSPCA)** \u2013 The objective of the SSPCA Scheme is to provide travel assistance registration fees to a team of minimum 2 to 10 students for attending competition at international level in order to encourage engineering students to improve their field of technical education. Students can apply online for SSPCA Scheme to avail its benefits.  \n [View Details](https://www.aicte-india.org/sites/default/files/SSPCA_Guidelines.pdf)  \n [Apply Online](https://www.aicte-india.org/sites/default/files/SSPCA%20Application%20Form%202019.pdf)", "009-listElement": "- **Prime Minister\u2019s Special Scholarship Scheme (PMSSS)** \u2013 Objective of PM Scholarship Scheme is to build up capacities in youth of J&K, educate, enable and empowering them to compete in normal course, enhancing and boosting employment potentials in students of J&K. Total 5000 scholarship are given @ Rs. 100000/- as Maintenance Charges and academic fee as Rs. 30000/- to General Degree, Rs. 125000/- to Engineering Degree & Rs. 300000/- to Medical Degree each year.  \n [View Details](https://www.aicte-india.org/bureaus/jk)", "010-listElement": "- **AICTE-INAE Travel Grant Scheme** \u2013 An AICTE-INAE Travel Grant Scheme for Engineering Students to present papers abroad has been launched for enhancing the quality of engineering education in the country. Students can apply online for AICTE-INAE Travel Grant Scheme or download pdf application form to avail its benefits.  \n [View Details](https://www.aicte-india.org/sites/default/files/1.%20Guidelines%20for%20AICTE%20-%20INAE%20Travel%20Grant%20Scheme.%20pdf.pdf)  \n [Apply Online](https://www.inae.in/aicte-inae-travel-grant-scheme-for-engineering-students-to-present-papers-abroad/)  \n [download pdf application form](https://www.aicte-india.org/sites/default/files/application%20form_2.pdf)", "011-listElement": "- **Smart India Hackathon 2019** \u2013 Smart India Hackathon is a unique initiative to identify new and disruptive digital solutions for solving the challenges faced by our country under the program of Smart India Hackathon 2017. This event was held on 1st \u2013 2nd April 2017 for 36 hrs non-stop competition. 9544 technology students, 598 problems statements, 29 different central govt. ministries, 26 different Nodal centres & funding of Rs. 3 Lakh per team for 100 qualified teams.  \n [View Details](https://www.aicte-india.org/Initiatives/smart-india-hackathon)", "012-listElement": "- **M.TECH Projects as Internship with Small and Medium Enterprises (MSMEs)** \u2013 The main objective of the scheme is to nurture an innovation ecosystem that benefits the technologically deficient MSMEs and technical institutes both. 408 Small and Medium Enterprises have given requirement of 738 Technology students.", "013-normal": "The list of PM Modi Yojana for students which are run All India Council for Technical Education are available at <https://www.aicte-india.org/> which is the official website."}, "003-section": {"000-title": "MHRD Run Education Schemes in India", "001-normal": "Here is the complete list of education schemes in India run by Ministry of Human Resource Development (MHRD):-", "